      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) below 5% on scalar stress-weighted hemolysis index across three systematically refined meshes, with Richardson extrapolation applied to the primary QoI.",
      "rationale": "A mesh sensitivity study was conducted using coarse, medium, and fine meshes (3.2M, 8.1M, and 18.4M elements). The hemolysis index showed acceptable qualitative convergence between medium and fine meshes, with differences below 8% on integrated hemolysis metrics. Engineering judgment supports that the medium mesh captures the dominant flow features driving hemolysis prediction. Given the comparative nature of the analysis (RH index relative to predicate), absolute discretization error is considered acceptable for decision-making purposes."
    },
