      "acceptanceCriteria": "The simulated QoI (scalar stress-weighted hemolysis index, RH) directly maps to the clinical acceptance criterion (RH < 1 relative to predicate).",
      "rationale": "The relative hemolysis index RH is the primary QoI and directly corresponds to the regulatory acceptance criterion. The stress-based hemolysis power-law model (Giersiepen-Wurzinger) is the established approach for CFD hemolysis prediction in this device class."
